args: Ahhh, but this sea breeze does feel divine.
It has been one battle after another lately;\nwe've scarce had time to catch our breath.
Is it so terrible a thing to take a moment\nof rest and relaxation when one can?
*sigh* Oh, how beautiful Elly looks\nsurrounded by all that sand.
No summer bloom can match the beauty\nof my Elly—nay, not even the sun itself!
Was that a sigh? Is she weary?!
She certainly has every right to be;\nthe path of a Paladyn is a harsh one.
And she has walked that path for years\nand years—a heavy burden indeed!
We'll not be at the shore for long,\nso it is essential she be able to\nenjoy this hard-earned holiday.
But what can I do to bring Elly the relief\nand relaxation she so richly deserves?
Perhaps she'd enjoy an ocean swim?\n...No, that might only exhaust her further.
Clearly sunbathing is the answer!\n...Ah, but what if she gets burned?
Blast! I fear this is beyond me.
Hmm... I see she has yet to remove\nher top outer layer.
As a Paladyn, she might consider it\nimmodest to show more skin than\nabsolutely necessary.
...Yet by the goddess, look at ME!
She must think me a vulgarity of the\nhighest order to be dressed so!
I specifically brought my finest suit so as\nnot to embarrass myself in front of Elly,\nyet perhaps it was still a mistake.
You've been mumbling to yourself for a\nlong time now, Julietta. Everything okay?
How long have you been standing there?!
I just walked over now, actually.\nYou looked sort of distraught,\nand I wanted to see if I could help.
D-distraught?! I am not distraught at all!\nI'm perfectly traught! One hundred percent!
Soooo I DIDN'T just overhear you say\nsomething about your swimsuit maybe\nbeing too ostentatious?
Y-Your Highness, I am a Paladyn!\nI would not trouble myself with\nsuch trivial concerns!
It would not even occur to me to worry\nif Elly thought I looked like the lowest\nvillage guttersnipe in this suit!
That thought is literally the furthest\nthought from my mind.
Wait, is THAT what you're worried about?
Well, I think you can relax. Elly told me\nearlier that she likes your suit.
M-might I trouble you with a query,\nPrince {player_name}?
Do you know what manner\nof holiday Elly enjoys?
Actually, I don't think it's ever come up.
(This is even worse than I thought...\nShe must be in fearsome need of a break!)
M-merely because I want to be certain\nthat Elly enjoys our summer holiday!
It's nice to see how much\nyou care about her.
I owe her my very life.
I would do absolutely anything for her.
And yet, I fear I have no idea what\nconstitutes a proper relaxing holiday.
It's not that complicated—people just\nwant to hang out and be together.
I require more tangible advice than that!
Look, have you ever been to the beach?
Of course. My family went on vacation\nto the beach every year.
I have many happy memories\nof those times.
Then why not invite Elisanne to do\nthe things you remember enjoying?
Because she may not find them\nas enjoyable as I did.
And what if she turns me down entirely?!
She's not the sort to refuse\nan invitation from a friend.
I will take your advice and extend\nan invitation to Elly this instant!
I really hope this turns out well for...\nHuh. She's coming back.
Y-Your Highness, what should I DO?!
Uh, talk to Elly? That WAS the plan, right?
Yes, but I got so nervous when I\napproached that I turned tail and fled!
Well, I guess I can...come with you?
*sigh* What am I getting myself into?
